<div id=3D"mw-content-text" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"mw-content-ltr=
"><p>A <b>hogshead</b> is an old unit of measurement. It was used to figure=
 out how much liquid, like wine or beer, could fit into a large barrel. Peo=
ple used hogsheads in many parts of Europe, but the exact size of a hogshea=
d could be different from one place to another. For example, a hogshead in =
England might hold a different amount than one in France.</p>
<p>In modern times, a hogshead is usually thought of as holding about 63 <a=
 href=3D"https://kids.kiddle.co/Gallon" title=3D"Gallon">gallons</a> in the=
 United States. This unit was even mentioned in an episode of <i>The Simpso=
ns</i>, which helped some people learn about it!</p>
<p></p>
