</div></div>
<h3><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"How_Big_is_a_Hogshead.3F">How Big is =
a Hogshead?</span></h3>
<p>The size of a hogshead changed a lot over time and in different places. =
For example, a hogshead of wine in England was usually 63 gallons. But a ho=
gshead of beer might be 54 gallons. This could be confusing!</p>
<h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Standardizing_the_Hogshead">Standardi=
zing the Hogshead</span></h4>
<p>To make things simpler, countries worked together to agree on standard m=
easurements. In 1959, countries like Canada, New Zealand, the United Kingdo=
m, and the United States signed a treaty. This agreement helped to standard=
ize many units, including the hogshead, making sure everyone used the same =
size.</p>
